description:
Kirsty Young, Huw Edwards and Dermot O'Leary reflect on the key moments of the day's royal wedding between Prince Harry and Meghan Markle. Highlights include the arrival of HM the Queen, senior members of the royal family and the star-studded wedding guests. There is the first glimpse of the bride in her stunning wedding dress, the marriage ceremony held in the intimate surroundings of the historic St George's Chapel and the magnificent sight of the newlyweds' carriage procession around the streets of Windsor, cheered on by thousands of jubilant spectators. In the studio, the team are joined by some of those lucky enough to have attended the celebrations and by those who played a significant part in this special day.
